            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">DO NOT INITIALIZE THIS CLASS OR ANY OF THIS SUBCLASSES
The symmetry equivalency assertion class is meant to enable assertions of  crystollograhpic equivalence between single crystallographic direction /plane and family of directions/planes if the equivalence applies for the given crystal symmetry. This class is part of the &quot;inference engine&quot;</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">symmetry equivalency assertion</rdfs:label>
        <owl:deprecated rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</owl:deprecated>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Symmetry equivalency assertion is an information content entity which is used to infer crystallographic equivalence between single crystallographic direction /plane and family of directions/planes if the equivalence applies for the given crystal symmetry.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


